<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-285-304  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 285 304.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Graphics World  May 1989 v12 n5 p36(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Flexibility for architects. (Intergraph Corp's Modelview)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pfitzer, Gary.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Intergraph Corp will announce interesting improvements to itsModelview ray-tracing and animation package.andP;  The upgrades willhelp architects with raster data and provide more interactivity inthe selection of textures and colors.andP;  One improvement is Escher,which allows photographs or video images to be scanned intoModelview.andP;  Another improvement is Pixie, which allows users tochange textures and colors interactively in a ray-traced image.andO;The newly enhanced Modelview package will cost $3,000 and will beavailable on all Intergraph Clipper workstations.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Intergraph Corp. (product enhancement).andO;Product:   Modelview (Computer program) (product enhancement).andO;Topic:     ArchitectureGraphics SoftwareEnhancementsScanningComputer GraphicsAnimationRay Tracing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>